Andy, what's up?
What are you workin' on?

07:32.552 --> 07:34.554
I'm concerned
With the baby.

07:34.554 --> 07:36.556
Why, he don't feel good?
Uh--

07:36.556 --> 07:40.760
She had him taken in
For some tests. He--
He got no resistance.

07:41.227 --> 07:43.296
What, to colds?
He don't fight 'em off.

07:43.796 --> 07:46.365
He's six months old.
 He's had seven colds.

07:46.365 --> 07:48.868
Sylvia took him in
For the tests
Unbeknownst to me.

07:48.868 --> 07:50.803
-when are you supposed
 To find out about that?
- later on.

07:51.237 --> 07:52.738
She's got us goin' in
To see his doctor.

07:53.239 --> 07:55.141
Today?
Yeah.

07:55.541 --> 07:58.544
Hey.
Hey! Gun!
Gun, andy!

07:58.544 --> 08:00.679
Hey! Hey, hey!
Hey! Stop!

08:02.764 --> 08:05.483
Police! Hold it!
Police! Freeze!

08:16.828 --> 08:19.748
Suspect's gone up
To the second floor!

08:19.748 --> 08:22.000
-[ women screaming ]
- which window?

08:22.000 --> 08:24.035
I don't know!

08:26.871 --> 08:29.974
[ screaming continues:
  Distorted, echoing ]

08:33.378 --> 08:35.246
[ gunshot ]

08:40.018 --> 08:41.619
[ echoing ]
Andy!

08:48.943 --> 08:51.229
- [ gasping ]
- andy!

08:51.229 --> 08:54.399
You hit?
Are you hit?

08:54.399 --> 08:57.569
Out the window.
[ screaming continues ]

08:59.871 --> 09:02.957
[ screaming, sobbing ]

09:02.957 --> 09:05.210
Be still. You're all right.
Just be still.

09:05.710 --> 09:07.829
You all right?
Out the window.
 Out the win--

09:08.329 --> 09:10.215
Andy, are you hurt?
You got shortness
Of breath?

09:10.215 --> 09:13.001
No. Now help simone.

09:13.001 --> 09:15.553
-[ screaming, sobbing ]
-[ sipowicz ] you're all right.

09:15.553 --> 09:18.973
[ screaming, sobbing
  Continue ]
You're all right now.

09:25.230 --> 09:28.066
[ no audible dialogue ]

09:28.066 --> 09:30.518
-can you help me
 With this?
- no. Leave me alone.

09:31.352 --> 09:33.772
Your partner okay?

09:34.272 --> 09:36.074
Yeah. Thanks a lot, sarge.
We'll put in a 6-1
At the house.

09:36.074 --> 09:37.992
[ murmurs ]

09:38.493 --> 09:40.612
This is laila edmonds, bobby.
She recognized the polaroid.

09:40.612 --> 09:43.915
Tell him what you know,
Ma'am.
His name was afro.

09:43.915 --> 09:47.285
Do you know what his last name
Was, miss edmonds?
No. He was just "afro."

09:47.786 --> 09:49.788
I don't know why somebody
Would want to do this
To him.

09:49.788 --> 09:52.290
You know where
This afro lives?
Down the street a little.

09:52.791 --> 09:54.793
My son knows.
Arthur.

09:56.594 --> 09:59.964
Miss edmonds, were you on
The street here when this man
Was running away from us?

09:59.964 --> 10:02.767
No, i wasn't. I heard
He took a shot at you.

10:02.767 --> 10:05.770
Arthur, somebody
Killed afro.
Is that right?

10:05.770 --> 10:07.772
Your mom says maybe you know
Where this afro lived.

10:08.273 --> 10:09.724
Yeah. Yeah, just
Down the block.

10:09.724 --> 10:12.310
You wanna
Point it out to us?
Yeah, okay.

10:12.811 --> 10:14.562
Andy.

10:14.562 --> 10:19.450
Bobby, when i showed this kid
The picture, he said he didn't
Know the d.o.a.

10:19.818 --> 10:21.870
I guess i didn't get
A good look before.

10:21.870 --> 10:24.405
Yeah, that happens a lot.
Come on.

10:27.041 --> 10:29.460
Excuse me, ma'am. Police.
I need to ask you
Some questions.

10:29.961 --> 10:31.796
Did you see what happened
On the street before?
No.

10:31.796 --> 10:33.715
How about this guy?
You ever seen him?
No. Sorry.

10:33.715 --> 10:37.001
Hey.

10:37.001 --> 10:38.837
That arthur
With the other cops--
He was in on it.

10:38.837 --> 10:41.756
On what?
What happened to afro.

10:41.756 --> 10:44.259
Last night,
Him and two other guys
Were carrying the trunk...

10:44.259 --> 10:46.761
In the picture
That you showed
Out of afro's building.

10:46.761 --> 10:50.014
What's your name?
It's got nothin'
To do with me.

10:50.014 --> 10:52.350
But that arthur--
He was a part of it.

10:57.355 --> 10:59.858
[ sirens wails ]

11:01.693 --> 11:04.696
[ woman ]
No warrant-- i don't need
To let you be lookin' around.

11:04.696 --> 11:06.831
C.s.u.'s on the way.
I know my rights.

11:07.332 --> 11:10.201
[ simone ]
We appreciate the cooperation.
He was in the vietnam war.

11:10.201 --> 11:13.705
Need help with your garbage
Or the snow, he'd just
Do that for you.

11:13.705 --> 11:15.623
I got james
Keepin' an eye on arthur.

11:16.124 --> 11:19.210
Wore that hat and pin for
Africa, but never put it in
Your face like some of 'em.

11:19.210 --> 11:21.429
- did afro use drugs?
- i wouldn't know about that.

11:21.429 --> 11:25.183
Bobby.
This could be a handle
Off the footlocker.

11:25.683 --> 11:28.603
This looks like
The rest of the newspaper
We found on the body.

11:29.103 --> 11:31.890
Anything in here
Belongs to me.
This is my building.

11:31.890 --> 11:36.311
You want half the sundaypost?
Well, afro got no relatives,
And he owed me money.

11:36.311 --> 11:38.980
We're lookin' for evidence,
Rosalie. Now, if somebody
Were to come back in...

11:38.980 --> 11:41.532
After we seal the place up,
That'd be up to them.

11:41.799 --> 11:43.534
Any money in here
Is mine.

11:43.534 --> 11:45.320
I don't usually hit women,
But i don't mind,

11:45.320 --> 11:47.705
'Cause when they hit back,
It don't really
Amount to much.

11:48.206 --> 11:50.491
-he threatened me!
- calm down, rosalie.

11:50.742 --> 11:52.493
You guys'll wait
For c.s.u.?
Yeah.

11:52.493 --> 11:55.246
Andy, we should go
Talk to arthur.
Yeah.

11:55.246 --> 11:58.132
Good luck with the toss.

11:58.132 --> 12:01.135
Get abused
For cooperation.

12:01.135 --> 12:05.640
[ martinez ]
That's all you can remember?
Okay, uh--

12:07.475 --> 12:10.478
Did you find
Any clues up there?
We found some things.

12:10.478 --> 12:13.932
I'm wondering if maybe
We can talk a little more at
The station house, miss edmonds.

12:13.932 --> 12:15.900
I don't know how much more
We can tell you.

12:15.900 --> 12:17.769
Actually, we probably got
All we need from you.

12:17.769 --> 12:22.073
Maybe we can get arthur here
To give us a little more
On afro's background.

12:22.073 --> 12:25.360
Well, whatever we can do
To help you catch
Whoever did this.

12:25.360 --> 12:27.695
We'll be glad to.
Good. What do you
Say, arthur?

12:27.695 --> 12:30.665
A little more
Background there
Maybe you can help us with?

12:30.665 --> 12:34.035
Take a ride with us
In to the station house?

12:34.035 --> 12:37.038
Okay, sure.
Good.
Car's right here.

12:37.038 --> 12:39.040
Thank you, ma'am.

12:52.704 --> 12:54.656
[ chattering ]

13:01.996 --> 13:03.998
Right up here.

13:03.998 --> 13:06.334
What do you think
Happened to andy?
I don't know.

13:06.834 --> 13:09.337
He said he wasn't
Short of breath.
Right.

13:09.337 --> 13:12.840
You know, i shouldn't scapegoat
Him on my weight gain.
Uh-huh.

13:12.840 --> 13:15.893
Another factor's
My new apartment--
Havin' my own kitchen.

13:15.893 --> 13:17.895
Yeah, availability
Of snacks.

13:17.895 --> 13:22.233
James, would you consider
Sharin' a diet with me?

13:22.233 --> 13:24.936
Just for gettin' me started.
Hey, greg, i'm runnin'
For delegate.

13:24.936 --> 13:26.938
I talk with the guys
All the time over doughnuts.

13:27.438 --> 13:29.440
Yeah. Hang back,
They could take it
For uppity.

13:29.440 --> 13:32.360
That gina's
Some cute girl, huh?

13:32.360 --> 13:35.580
The new p.a.a. In anticrime.
Yeah. She seems
Very appealing.

13:35.580 --> 13:38.416
Anticrime gets her,
And we get roseanne.

13:38.916 --> 13:41.202
Which is a reference
To what, james?
Our new p.a.a.

13:41.202 --> 13:44.422
- but roseanne in what sense?
- greg, what are you
  Gettin' all excited about?

13:44.922 --> 13:47.008
Because the new p.a.a.
Carries some extra poundage,

13:47.008 --> 13:48.843
She's disqualified
From the human community?

13:48.843 --> 13:51.679
Absolutely not.
I'll tell ya, james.

13:51.679 --> 13:53.681
It's an accumulation
Of remarks over
The course of a day...

13:54.182 --> 13:56.184
That contribute
To an atmosphere
And an attitude.

13:56.184 --> 13:58.186
And i wish people
Would realize.

13:58.186 --> 13:59.971
Fine. I'd never say that
To her face, greg.

13:59.971 --> 14:02.857
You said it to my face, james.
All right. Greg.

14:04.358 --> 14:06.360
I speak for all fat people.

14:06.360 --> 14:10.198
- how's it goin'?
- hi. I'm geri turner,
  The new p.a.a.

14:10.198 --> 14:11.866
-bobby simone.
 This is andy sipowicz.
- how's it goin'?

14:11.866 --> 14:13.568
-diane russell.
- hey.

14:14.068 --> 14:16.037
Which interview's open?
They all are.

14:16.537 --> 14:20.825
Did i understand
That you got shot at?
Yeah. I'm all right.

14:20.825 --> 14:22.710
Come on.
Let's talk in here.

14:22.710 --> 14:26.247
-[ phone ringing ]
-[ geri ]
  Fifteenth detective squad.

14:26.247 --> 14:30.551
So andy got shot at?
Yeah. We got a tip the dump job
Was loaded up on 14th street.

14:30.551 --> 14:33.805
We go around there
To show the picture. This guy
Just books off the street.

14:33.805 --> 14:35.973
He throws two shots at andy
Inside a building.

14:35.973 --> 14:38.259
We chased him,
But he got away.
Who'd you bring back?

14:38.760 --> 14:42.647
There was a woman on canvass
That made him one of the guys
Who put the d.o.a. In the van.

14:42.647 --> 14:44.766
He don't know
We like him yet.
Andy's okay?

14:46.184 --> 14:47.985
Yeah.

14:50.354 --> 14:52.657
River cafeיי, huh?
7:30?

14:52.657 --> 14:54.992
Are you readin' stuff
Off my desk here?

14:54.992 --> 14:57.445
If you don't want it read, pal,
Don't leave it written.

14:57.445 --> 15:01.199
[ scoffs ] do you wanna
Sit in on this with us?
Yeah, all right.

15:01.199 --> 15:05.119
Now, andy didn't get
Chest pains or something,
Did he?

15:05.119 --> 15:08.923
No. He's okay.
No? 'Cause he didn't
Go after that guy.

15:08.923 --> 15:12.426
He's half worried about theo.
They're runnin' some kind
Of tests on him.

15:12.426 --> 15:15.096
- 'cause he gets
  So many colds?
- yes.

15:15.096 --> 15:17.098
Are they concerned?
Should i call sylvia?

15:17.598 --> 15:19.600
I don't know.
I didn't wanna push him
With it, you know?

15:19.600 --> 15:22.603
So andy was probably
Just halfway distracted.

15:22.603 --> 15:25.056
[ door opens ]

15:28.059 --> 15:31.195
- arthur says he didn't really
  Know afro that well.
- that's right.

15:32.613 --> 15:35.616
Yeah.

15:35.616 --> 15:39.620
I'm gonna tell you somethin'
Up front, arthur. We know
You had dealings with afro.

15:39.620 --> 15:43.374
Now, if you were involved
With something that had
A bad outcome there,

15:43.374 --> 15:45.743
We're absolutely prepared
To hear what happened.

15:45.743 --> 15:48.246
You gotta put it into the proper
Light. Do not stand there
And lie to us, okay?

15:48.246 --> 15:52.216
- i wasn't involved.
- arthur, this case
  Is coming into place.

15:52.216 --> 15:56.337
Now, we know that you
Helped carry afro's body
Out of his apartment.

15:56.337 --> 15:58.089
We know that.
Oh, man.

15:58.089 --> 16:00.508
So that leads me to believe
Either one of two things--

16:00.508 --> 16:02.393
You killed him,
Or somebody else did it.

16:02.393 --> 16:05.897
For whatever reason,
You're covering for 'em.
Oh, man! Oh, man!

16:05.897 --> 16:07.732
And it'd better be
A good reason there,
Arthur.

16:07.732 --> 16:10.685
Because with
The evidence we have here--
The eyewitness testimony--

16:11.185 --> 16:12.987
Right now, it'syourarm
That's lookin' at that needle.

16:12.987 --> 16:17.074
Arthur. You are not
Under arrest here, okay?

16:17.074 --> 16:20.111
Now sit down
And tell us what happened.

16:25.449 --> 16:27.952
[ gasping ]

16:29.453 --> 16:32.924
My mother had nothin'
To do with it.
That-that's first off.

16:32.924 --> 16:36.594
- she didn't?
- oh, she's gonna kill me
  When she finds this out.

16:37.094 --> 16:41.515
- [ breathes deeply ] does she
  Have to find this out?
- arthur, tell us what happened.

16:41.515 --> 16:45.102
I didn't shoot anybody.
Afro came out to cop.

16:45.102 --> 16:47.889
[ sipowicz ]
Came out where?
Out to their corner.

16:47.889 --> 16:52.226
Uh, hector and rodney speck.
And he's got--

16:52.226 --> 16:54.729
He's flashin' around
All this money
Off his veteran check.

16:54.729 --> 16:57.565
How come he's gotta flash
That money around like that?
That's just stupid.

16:58.065 --> 17:01.452
So they took him up
To his place-- this, uh,
Hector and rodney speck?

17:01.452 --> 17:03.788
Yeah.
You went up there
With 'em?

17:03.788 --> 17:05.873
No. 'Cause i know
What hector's like.

17:05.873 --> 17:07.909
And with afro
Flashin' that money--

17:07.909 --> 17:09.911
I went home,
Tried to read the newspaper.

17:09.911 --> 17:12.914
Now, what time was this?
How long were you home?

17:12.914 --> 17:15.916
It was about, uh,
10:30 last night.

17:15.916 --> 17:19.136
Then they came and called me
From up the street, like,
Maybe 20 minutes later.

17:19.136 --> 17:21.137
Said to come meet them
Over at afro's.

17:21.137 --> 17:23.840
And-- and that's when
I seen what they done.

17:23.840 --> 17:26.394
Afro was already dead.
Afro was already dead.

17:26.394 --> 17:29.263
- and what'd they say?
- help 'em.

17:29.764 --> 17:31.649
Put him in newspaper
And fit him in the trunk.

17:31.649 --> 17:34.485
What'd they say
About killin' him?
I didn't wanna ask 'em.

17:34.485 --> 17:38.022
- but it was hector
  Who broke bad?
- hector's crazy.

17:38.022 --> 17:42.326
[ gasps ]
And then we stood in the doorway
Till the street come empty,

17:42.326 --> 17:44.528
And then we took him
 And put him in rodney's van.

17:44.528 --> 17:48.165
[ exhales ]
Why did you do this, arthur?
Why'd you help 'em?

17:48.165 --> 17:50.952
I was afraid if i didn't.

17:54.922 --> 17:57.291
Crack.

17:57.291 --> 18:01.595
They gave you some crack.
I got a problem over it.

18:02.797 --> 18:05.716
- my mother don't know.
- where'd you get the trunk?

18:05.716 --> 18:08.219
[ sighs ]
My brother had it
In the navy,

18:08.219 --> 18:10.221
But i told rodney
I'm not touchin' that.

18:10.721 --> 18:14.191
And then hector drops his end
And the handle breaks, so then
I had to help 'em.

18:14.191 --> 18:15.893
That's the only reason.

18:15.893 --> 18:18.863
So where are we gonna
Find these guys at?
They go to rodney's sister.

18:18.863 --> 18:21.532
She got a place
Over on 11th.

18:21.532 --> 18:23.367
You're gonna show us
Where she lives.

18:23.868 --> 18:26.620
She won't be there
Till tomorrow mornin'.
His sister works nights.

18:26.620 --> 18:28.739
And, uh, she won't
Give him a key.

18:31.208 --> 18:33.711
Does my mother
Have to hear about this?

18:33.711 --> 18:36.881
We'll make it sound good
For your mom.

18:42.420 --> 18:45.139
So when will he
Talk to us?

18:46.474 --> 18:48.926
[ sighs ]
Okay. Yeah.

18:49.427 --> 18:51.929
Uh, you want me
To bring you anything?

18:51.929 --> 18:53.931
All right. I'll see you
In a little bit then.

18:53.931 --> 18:57.101
But he does seem
More comfortable
To you, right?

18:57.101 --> 19:00.438
Yeah. All right.
[ handset settles
 In cradle ]

19:08.612 --> 19:11.832
- get arthur handed off?
- yeah. The d.a. Squad--
  They took him over to a motel.

19:13.617 --> 19:18.539
Diane, you think we should
Buff up a little bit
Before we go out?

19:18.539 --> 19:20.291
Is that what we're
Callin' it today?

19:20.291 --> 19:24.178
I'm talkin' about
Changin' clothes.
[ laughs ]

19:24.678 --> 19:27.381
Give me a couple minutes, huh?
Mm-hmm. Sure.

19:37.475 --> 19:39.477
He postponed on us--
The baby doctor.

19:39.977 --> 19:42.980
Said he needs
More tests back.
Yeah, huh?

19:42.980 --> 19:45.483
That's what he told sylvia.

19:48.903 --> 19:51.906
I apologize--
In that building.

19:51.906 --> 19:56.243
- forget about it, andy.
- yeah.

19:56.243 --> 19:58.746
Somebody had to stay
With those women, right?

20:00.247 --> 20:03.667
You're buyin' trouble, andy.
Theo's gonna be fine.

20:05.136 --> 20:08.472
Don't spill nothin'
On your shirt
Before you ask her.

20:13.394 --> 20:14.895
[ door closes ]

20:32.413 --> 20:35.416
How'd he seem?
His breathing's
A little easier.

20:35.416 --> 20:37.918
Almost an hour
Consecutive napping, right?

20:37.918 --> 20:40.204
Mm-hmm.

20:40.204 --> 20:43.124
How was your day?

20:43.124 --> 20:45.126
All right.

20:45.126 --> 20:49.130
So he sounded credible,
The pediatrician--
The tests not being back?

20:50.131 --> 20:52.133
Oh, yeah.
I'm just saying,

20:52.133 --> 20:54.635
He didn't sound like
 He was withholding nothin'?

20:54.635 --> 20:56.637
If he had given us
Partial results today,

20:56.637 --> 20:58.639
Would you still be fixated
On what we didn't get?

20:58.639 --> 21:00.357
These tests
Were your idea.

21:00.357 --> 21:03.694
These were you and him
With the seven colds
In the last six months.

21:03.694 --> 21:05.696
I know.

21:14.488 --> 21:17.491
They brought you
More folders today?

21:17.491 --> 21:19.493
Yeah. Just trying
To get current.

21:19.493 --> 21:21.495
You're still targeting
Next week?

21:21.495 --> 21:23.497
If anything's
Wrong with theo,
Of course i won't go back.

21:23.497 --> 21:25.299
But he said every reason
For optimism.

21:25.299 --> 21:28.219
He said that goin' in.
Can we stop
Worrying it, andy?

21:28.219 --> 21:31.972
We'll find out tomorrow.
We'll get the answers
Tomorrow, right?

21:37.394 --> 21:41.565
[ exhales ]
Don't cry.

21:41.565 --> 21:44.401
I know
That it's a lot of times
For a baby to be sick,

21:44.401 --> 21:46.270
And i know that
This is hard for you.

21:46.270 --> 21:50.407
But would you please
Just not make me
More worried? Okay?

21:50.407 --> 21:53.694
This was you
And the pediatrician--
Check the baby's immune system.

21:53.694 --> 21:56.197
I know.
It was your initiative.

21:56.197 --> 21:59.200
[ baby crying ]

22:38.571 --> 22:41.073
Thanks
For the dinner.

22:41.073 --> 22:43.075
Sure.

22:44.577 --> 22:46.579
[ sighs ]
What was the occasion?

22:47.079 --> 22:49.582
[ exhales ]

22:49.582 --> 22:51.584
[ laughs ]
Huh?

22:56.973 --> 22:59.976
I-- i'm not gonna come up
With anything original.

23:02.979 --> 23:04.981
Diane, i-- i want you
To marry me.

23:06.482 --> 23:09.435
[ exhales ]
Oh. Bobby.

23:11.437 --> 23:13.739
I-- i don't know
What to say.

23:15.107 --> 23:18.194
No?
I'm just surprised.

23:18.194 --> 23:20.696
I'm, uh--

23:21.197 --> 23:24.033
We've been so happy.
In my house, the married
People weren't like that.

23:26.953 --> 23:31.457
Look, diane, it's--
It's taken me a while
To realize this, but life--

23:31.457 --> 23:33.759
It's not just about
Losing things, you know?

23:33.759 --> 23:37.680
I want to be able
To add on to our life.

23:37.680 --> 23:40.466
We'd be a happy family.

23:43.386 --> 23:46.188
When do you want kids?

23:46.188 --> 23:48.190
Sounds like "soon"
Is not the right answer.

23:51.644 --> 23:53.646
[ sighs ]
Bobby.

23:53.646 --> 23:57.149
My mom shot my dad
Seven months ago.
I know that.

23:57.149 --> 23:59.035
I know that.

24:00.536 --> 24:03.039
Can i think about it?

24:03.039 --> 24:05.041
Yeah. Sure.

24:07.793 --> 24:09.795
Can i see the ring?
[ chuckles ]

24:16.719 --> 24:18.721
It's beautiful.

24:21.674 --> 24:23.676
Thanks.

24:24.510 --> 24:26.979
I love you, bobby.

24:36.772 --> 24:38.774
Okay.

24:41.277 --> 24:43.279
Okay.

25:03.749 --> 25:06.919
Great. Thank you very much.
Bye-bye.

25:06.919 --> 25:08.754
Detective, this attorney
Called for you.

25:08.754 --> 25:11.757
Yeah, thanks.

25:11.757 --> 25:13.926
Did he say with regards
To what case?

25:13.926 --> 25:16.846
No. I would have
Written that down.

25:16.846 --> 25:20.549
Good morning, andy.
Mornin'.

25:20.549 --> 25:22.601
Morning.

25:23.102 --> 25:24.887
Guy we wanna talk to
About afro's in 1.

25:24.887 --> 25:27.773
Oh, yeah?

25:27.773 --> 25:30.559
Took a possession collar
For crack.

25:34.397 --> 25:36.649
Did you ask her?

25:36.649 --> 25:40.069
Yeah. She's gonna
Think about it.

25:43.873 --> 25:45.875
Rodney speck.
Yeah.

25:45.875 --> 25:47.877
How you doin',
Rodney?
That wasn't my drugs.

25:47.877 --> 25:50.212
Somebody else dropped
That bag on the curb.
So this was a wrongful arrest?

25:50.212 --> 25:54.583
- hell, i don't use no crack.
- that's a new approach
  For you, right?

25:54.583 --> 25:57.303
You got three collars for crack
There on your sheet, rodney.

25:57.303 --> 26:00.723
[ sighs ]
I been done with that
Six months.

26:00.723 --> 26:04.060
What were you doin'
Two nights ago?
Nothin'. Hangin' around.

26:04.060 --> 26:06.762
- whereabouts?
- couple of places.

26:06.762 --> 26:09.482
-were you up
 On 14th street?
- a little while.

26:09.482 --> 26:12.485
Where you hangin' with hector,
Rodney, the little while
You were up there?

26:12.485 --> 26:15.321
- hangin' with afro?
- nope.

26:15.321 --> 26:17.606
No?
Arthur say i was?

26:17.606 --> 26:21.444
You think about who gave you up,
Rodney, not gettin' in front
Of this homicide.

26:21.444 --> 26:23.863
We know that you were
Involved with killing afro.

26:23.863 --> 26:26.532
Arthur can't put a gun
In anyone's hands, rodney.

26:26.532 --> 26:28.951
But you're gonna do this,
Or either hector is.

26:29.251 --> 26:32.338
I didn't kill nobody!
We got eyewitnesses
That put you there, rodney--

26:32.338 --> 26:34.507
During and after the fact.

26:34.507 --> 26:37.543
If hector pulled the trigger,
You gotta get that out.

26:37.543 --> 26:39.962
Rat him out,
Then do time with hector?

26:39.962 --> 26:41.964
Who says you're gonna be
In the same joint?

26:41.964 --> 26:46.435
If hector killed afro, rodney,
There must be some reason
That you stood by.

26:46.435 --> 26:48.721
Maybe you were in fear
For your life.

26:49.221 --> 26:53.559
[ scoffs ]
Man, believe that--
What i seen hector do.

26:53.559 --> 26:55.478
These other things
That you saw,

26:55.978 --> 26:58.981
You didn't try to stop 'em
'Cause they were just
Drug dealers, right?

26:58.981 --> 27:01.984
Hector takin' 'em off.
Here, he was takin' off
An innocent guy.

27:02.485 --> 27:06.322
You tried to stop him,
But you were in fear
For your life.

27:13.746 --> 27:16.415
He's crazy.

27:16.415 --> 27:18.717
You don't know
How crazy he is.

27:18.717 --> 27:20.970
You explain how many people
Hector killed,

27:20.970 --> 27:23.088
Where he created
A fear in you,

27:23.088 --> 27:25.841
The d.a.'s
Gonna understand that.

27:25.841 --> 27:28.344
Like when he shot
Them lupones.

27:28.344 --> 27:31.480
They were givin' it up,
But he did 'em anyway.
It was needless.

27:31.480 --> 27:33.482
Anybody else?
Drug rip-offs.

27:33.482 --> 27:35.768
Dino thompson--
He did him.

27:35.768 --> 27:37.903
He gets a rush off of it.

27:37.903 --> 27:40.356
He'll shoot it out with you.
He says it all the time.

27:40.356 --> 27:42.324
Five-o come,
He's drawin' down.

27:42.324 --> 27:45.194
Just tell us where we can
Look for hector, rodney.

27:45.194 --> 27:47.496
We'll take care of him
Drawin' down.

27:49.999 --> 27:52.334
I gotta give up
That other stuff too?
Yeah.

27:52.334 --> 27:54.620
You just, uh, compose
Your thoughts a little.

28:02.878 --> 28:05.014
I gotta meet sylvia
At the doctor's.

28:05.014 --> 28:07.516
I can stay.
Yeah? Thanks.

28:07.516 --> 28:11.520
Yeah. Then, uh, maybe i'll take
Greg and james-- we'll go
Look for this hector.

28:11.520 --> 28:14.523
I'll-- i'll be back.
Wait for me.

28:15.024 --> 28:17.026
Well, good luck, andy.

28:20.696 --> 28:22.698
How's it goin'?
Hi.

28:24.533 --> 28:30.039
- uh--
- so, um, what'd you get
  From rodney speck?

28:30.039 --> 28:32.374
He's gonna give up a statement,
Point us to the other guy.

28:36.078 --> 28:38.581
Good.

28:42.501 --> 28:46.889
- how's this gonna work?
- i've got a mouth full
  Of marbles.

28:46.889 --> 28:51.977
I tell you, i should just get
Back in the bag for being
A no kind of detective.

28:51.977 --> 28:54.847
-yeah? They should bust you
  Back to cop?
- yeah.

28:57.683 --> 28:59.518
I just never figured it
To go like this, diane.

29:03.188 --> 29:07.409
I'm sorry i couldn't give you
An answer right away.
Don't be sorry.

29:08.694 --> 29:11.530
I'll try to think fast.
[ chuckles ]

29:17.419 --> 29:20.606
???? [ woman vocalizing ]

29:31.300 --> 29:33.435
- it's all good news.
- [ sighs ] thank god.

29:33.435 --> 29:36.772
- all the tests are back?
- yeah, they're all back.

29:36.772 --> 29:40.809
I've told sylvia that these
Are not dangerous infections
Theo was getting.

29:40.809 --> 29:43.979
The worry was that he might
Have some problem that was
Lowering his resistance.

29:43.979 --> 29:47.199
This is the immune problem?
And his immune system
Is fine.

29:47.199 --> 29:50.119
His i.g.g. Is normal.
 His i.g.a. Is normal.

29:50.119 --> 29:52.371
He's a normal baby
Who's had a bunch of colds.

29:52.371 --> 29:54.456
Doctor,
We're so grateful.

29:54.456 --> 29:56.492
To be truthful, detective,

29:56.492 --> 29:59.328
With another baby,
I don't think i'd have
Ordered these tests yet.

29:59.328 --> 30:02.464
But i know, from sylvia,
That you're very concerned
About theo's well-being.

30:02.464 --> 30:05.250
Seven colds
In the last six months.

30:05.751 --> 30:09.805
Which is very understandable
In view of your recent loss.

30:09.805 --> 30:13.142
You a baby doctor
Or a psychiatrist?
Andy.

30:13.142 --> 30:16.812
I'm a baby doctor
Who's telling you
This son is healthy...

30:16.812 --> 30:21.266
And that happy children grow up
In an atmosphere of trust.

30:21.266 --> 30:23.185
Which includes
Believing in the future...

30:23.686 --> 30:26.822
Even though we know
There are no guarantees.

30:28.824 --> 30:30.826
I guess that makes sense.

30:33.445 --> 30:36.448
Thank you.
Enjoy your baby.

30:37.282 --> 30:40.336
Thanks for your interest.

30:59.388 --> 31:01.223
Hey. Hello.

31:01.223 --> 31:03.559
Hi, detective.
Yeah.

31:03.892 --> 31:05.561
James martinez.
Gina, right?

31:05.561 --> 31:08.197
Gina colon.
Yeah, like the perfume.

31:08.197 --> 31:10.566
So, uh, how you
Settlin' in upstairs?

31:10.566 --> 31:14.787
I think pretty good. I look
At the 61's for patterns
And also the 2-50's.

31:14.787 --> 31:17.239
That's good. Sure. Yeah.
So did you get
Your new p.a.a.?

31:17.239 --> 31:20.626
Oh, yeah. Her name's geri.
Heavyset woman.

31:20.626 --> 31:22.661
Well, take care, james.

31:22.661 --> 31:24.663
Yeah. You take care, gina.

31:31.387 --> 31:34.089
[ geri ] these are
Your messages, detective.
Yeah, thanks.

31:35.974 --> 31:39.011
Hey, how'd it go?
Uh, good.

31:39.011 --> 31:41.013
The immune system's good.

31:41.013 --> 31:43.515
Uh, the colds themselves--

31:44.016 --> 31:46.268
He says he was never really
Even worried about them.

31:46.268 --> 31:48.404
God bless, huh?

31:50.906 --> 31:54.193
- ready?
- yeah.

31:54.193 --> 31:58.030
Greg, james. You wanna check
One of these possibles
On our second perp?

31:58.030 --> 32:01.033
- sure.
- i'll go out with you.
- that's good.

32:02.701 --> 32:05.204
- you gonna ride with them?
- yeah.

32:17.466 --> 32:19.768
My son made it over
From storage.

32:19.768 --> 32:21.603
Didn't know
He rented it out.

32:22.104 --> 32:24.389
This is where hector is?
To the left.

32:24.389 --> 32:26.725
No second exit
Because of storage.

32:29.228 --> 32:32.231
Don't put me in trouble
With the buildin' inspectors.

32:32.231 --> 32:34.616
Go on upstairs now.

32:44.793 --> 32:46.295
You wanna take it?

32:46.795 --> 32:48.797
Yeah. Let me take it.

32:58.006 --> 32:59.808
[ grunts ]

32:59.808 --> 33:01.810
Hey!

33:01.810 --> 33:03.395
Police!
[ groans ]

33:05.264 --> 33:07.399
- [ groans ]
- you're done! You're done!

33:09.184 --> 33:11.487
I nearly got you too, pig.

33:11.487 --> 33:13.989
Yeah. I'm the one you threw
The shots at, hector.
I got the gun.

33:13.989 --> 33:16.275
- you didn't hide like a bitch,
  I'd have took your ass out!
- shut up!

33:16.275 --> 33:21.163
Oh, sticks and stones, hector.
Now we'll see how your bones
Hold up. Come on.

33:42.150 --> 33:44.987
Move down right there.
I ain't goin' for nothin'.

33:44.987 --> 33:47.239
And you better not
Take off these cuffs.

33:47.239 --> 33:49.825
Then we're gonna find out
How bad you are,
Right, hector?

33:49.825 --> 33:51.994
Yeah. Pisses on himself again.
[ laughing ]

33:51.994 --> 33:53.829
This guy's beautiful.

33:54.329 --> 33:55.948
Hide like a little bitch
When i drew my gun.

33:55.948 --> 33:58.200
Where you gonna hide at
This time?
You better shut your mouth!

33:58.200 --> 34:00.919
Bobby. Take his cuffs off.

34:02.504 --> 34:05.374
What, you both gonna
Pistol-whip me?
You got guns.

34:05.874 --> 34:08.677
Come on. Go ahead. Who gonna
Hit me first? Which side?

34:10.212 --> 34:12.848
Take this outside.

34:12.848 --> 34:15.516
Hector and i
Gotta consult.

34:19.938 --> 34:22.440
[ door closes ]

34:25.193 --> 34:27.362
[ drawer closes ]

34:37.456 --> 34:39.958
[ vehicles passing ]

34:39.958 --> 34:43.543
Okay, scumbag. It's me
Between you and the window.
Let's see how tough you are.

34:43.543 --> 34:45.462
Yeah, i take you,
And then they kill me.

34:45.462 --> 34:47.965
Nobody's comin' in here.
You get through me, you're
Outside on the streets.

34:48.465 --> 34:50.467
Then they shoot me down.

34:50.967 --> 34:54.170
I don't know, hector.
I'm hearin' a lot of
Words here, you know?

34:54.170 --> 34:56.672
You don't even
Get to your feet.

34:57.674 --> 34:59.510
Is it like this, hector--

34:59.510 --> 35:03.347
When you got the drop,
You throw shots,
Or else you just talk?

35:03.347 --> 35:05.015
Kiss my ass, pig.

35:05.015 --> 35:07.735
Talk and don't even stand up
With the window
Right over there.

35:07.735 --> 35:12.322
You hid... Like a little woman.
We both gonna know that.

35:14.441 --> 35:16.944
I was afraid, hector.
[ laughs ]

35:16.944 --> 35:19.947
I used to figure you went
When your time came,
And no point worrying.

35:19.947 --> 35:22.449
Now i'm afraid to die.

35:24.952 --> 35:26.954
Make me hide again.

35:30.758 --> 35:33.260
Come on.

35:33.761 --> 35:36.263
Stand up, you gutless
Piece of crap.

35:39.183 --> 35:42.019
Yo, where my lawyer at, man?
I take my lawyer now.

35:43.520 --> 35:45.889
You want a lawyer, huh?
You don't wanna go
For the window?

35:45.889 --> 35:48.275
I want a lawyer!

35:48.275 --> 35:51.612
Sure, hector.
Two eyewitnesses.

35:51.612 --> 35:54.114
We can live without
Your statement.

35:54.114 --> 35:56.617
But you just remember this,
Sweetheart.

35:57.117 --> 35:59.119
You got your cuffs off
Like you wanted.

35:59.119 --> 36:01.121
You folded.

36:01.121 --> 36:03.457
And this bitch
Never even touched you.

36:13.383 --> 36:15.385
Hector wants a lawyer.

36:21.175 --> 36:24.178
Get up.
Turn around.

36:40.027 --> 36:41.912
[ exhales ]

36:46.667 --> 36:49.536
My god.
[ sighs ]

36:50.037 --> 36:52.039
My god, andy.
What's goin' on?

36:52.039 --> 36:55.542
My weight.
It can't be any more than it was
Five minutes ago, medavoy.

36:56.043 --> 36:58.045
I just confirmed
My worst fears.

36:58.045 --> 37:02.049
I weigh 196 pounds
At 5 foot
7 and a half inches.

37:03.550 --> 37:05.552
That is a lot.

37:05.552 --> 37:08.856
I gotta do something--
Maybe join a weight group.

37:08.856 --> 37:11.024
[ sighs ]
You wanna start
The competition tomorrow?

37:11.024 --> 37:14.027
That's got no credibility,
Andy.

37:14.027 --> 37:17.231
We canceled that four times.
We'll absolutely
Start tomorrow.

37:17.231 --> 37:18.615
Yeah?
Yeah.

37:18.615 --> 37:21.151
'Cause i'd so much
Rather keep it in-house.

37:21.151 --> 37:25.572
Seven pounds a month
Or a $200 forfeit to
The other kid's college account,

37:25.572 --> 37:29.743
Plus a 250 overall prize
To the other kid's account
At the end of the competition.

37:29.743 --> 37:32.713
That-that's so perfect, andy.

37:32.713 --> 37:35.499
That's a win-win.
Yeah.
That's what we'll do.

37:40.671 --> 37:42.923
You wanna hop on now,
Get a preview?

37:43.423 --> 37:46.476
No. 8:00 a.m.
Be here with your scale.

37:46.476 --> 37:48.478
Okay. Good, andy.

37:53.734 --> 37:58.105
We gotta send a big hello
To those assholes
In the 13th.

37:58.105 --> 38:00.607
Let 'em know
We collared up.
Oh, yeah.

38:02.442 --> 38:05.162
[ geri ]
Fifteenth detective squad.
May i help you?

38:05.162 --> 38:07.164
She express
Some hesitation--
Russell?

38:08.665 --> 38:12.035
Yeah. I don't know
Where it's going, andy.

38:12.035 --> 38:16.924
That girl loves you.
I'll tell you that
Straight out.

38:16.924 --> 38:19.376
Yeah, well, we'll see
Where it goes.

38:20.377 --> 38:22.296
Right now,
I'm not too optimistic.

38:22.796 --> 38:24.464
Yo. Where's detective simone?

38:24.464 --> 38:27.100
- may i say
  What this is regarding?
- i'm detective simone.

38:27.100 --> 38:29.886
- hey, who are you?
- didn't you just
  Ask to see me?

38:29.886 --> 38:32.222
- where does she get off
  Leaving you that building?
- hey. Change your tone,

38:32.723 --> 38:34.641
Or you're gonna get thrown
Back down those stairs,
Okay?

38:34.641 --> 38:36.893
What's your name?
Henry coffield.
She left you that building.

38:36.893 --> 38:39.646
- teresa coffield.
- here, sit down.

38:39.646 --> 38:44.284
I don't wanna sit down.
That's my mother. That
Building's supposed to be mine.

38:44.284 --> 38:47.287
My wife was maria cimino.
I used to clean her buildings
On the weekends.

38:47.287 --> 38:49.156
Teresa--
 Teresa was her aunt.

38:49.156 --> 38:52.492
Yeah, that's real heartwarming.
That definitely lets you
Jew me out of the building.

38:52.492 --> 38:54.294
Say your name again.
Henry.

38:54.294 --> 38:56.964
Henry, put a civil tongue
In your mouth and listen
To what i'm tellin' you.

38:57.464 --> 39:00.751
I know nothin' about this.
Did you talk to louis d'amico?

39:00.751 --> 39:03.420
He's a lawyer.
He's taking care
Of my mother's will.

39:03.420 --> 39:06.340
I got a message from him.
That's what this is about.

39:06.340 --> 39:09.676
And i'm asking you
To do the right thing. I'm
Supposed to have that building.

39:09.676 --> 39:12.346
I counted on it,
And i'm screwed up real good
If i don't get it.

39:12.346 --> 39:14.598
I'll call him up.
Wouldyou call him up?

39:14.598 --> 39:19.019
Try to do the right thing,
'Cause otherwise you're gonna
Ruin someone's life.

39:34.251 --> 39:37.037
[ equipment humming ]

39:39.006 --> 39:41.458
[ clears throat ]

39:44.461 --> 39:45.962
[ punching buttons ]

39:51.468 --> 39:54.438
- were you usin' this today?
- no, uh-uh.

39:54.438 --> 39:57.808
Yeah, 'cause it was workin'
This mornin'.
Well, i wasn't on it.

39:57.808 --> 40:02.646
- gonna wanna use this?
-[ door closes ]

40:02.646 --> 40:05.949
Nah. I'm just, uh,
Lookin' in.

40:05.949 --> 40:09.703
They got this stuff from
That murdered dealer's
Place, huh?

40:09.703 --> 40:12.406
That, uh, vasquez?
At least he died in shape.

40:12.406 --> 40:15.325
Yeah.
[ chuckles ]

40:15.325 --> 40:19.212
- abby sullivan.
- yeah. Greg medavoy.

40:19.212 --> 40:21.498
Just got transferred to rip.

40:21.498 --> 40:24.251
I-i'm with the squad.

40:24.751 --> 40:27.471
Hope property
Never releases this stuff.
Yeah. [ chuckles ]

40:29.473 --> 40:32.059
Uh, good to meet you,
Abby.

40:32.059 --> 40:35.512
- you're not gonna work out?
- nah, uh-uh.

40:35.812 --> 40:38.432
Although, you know, i--
I'm definitely thinkin'
Of tonin' up.

40:38.432 --> 40:40.350
Takin' off some pounds.

40:40.350 --> 40:43.770
Yeah. I've even got a bet
Goin' with a friend, you know?

40:43.770 --> 40:45.522
Uh, weight-loss competition.

40:45.522 --> 40:49.192
Long trip-- small steps.
Yeah.

40:49.192 --> 40:53.196
Yeah. I like that.
That's, uh--

40:53.196 --> 40:55.082
That's better than
Old dogs-- new tricks.

40:55.082 --> 40:57.033
[ chuckles ]

40:57.033 --> 41:00.253
See ya.

41:08.678 --> 41:11.681
Okay. Okay, i guess we'll
Talk about all this
In the morning.

41:11.681 --> 41:13.683
Thank you. Yeah.

41:13.683 --> 41:17.604
What'd the lawyer say?

41:17.604 --> 41:20.474
She left me the building.

41:20.474 --> 41:22.476
I guess there's a bunch
Of notes against it.

41:22.476 --> 41:26.980
Oh, and here i was thinking
You might be rich.
Yeah, huh?

41:26.980 --> 41:30.484
Would that have
Moved me up?

41:32.452 --> 41:34.454
[ clears throat ]
Bobby?

41:34.454 --> 41:36.323
What about, like,
An open-ended engagement?

41:36.323 --> 41:39.793
[ scoffs ]

41:39.793 --> 41:42.796
You mean, like, we're engaged
But not to be married?

41:42.796 --> 41:44.664
My mom and dougie still
Need a lot of my attention.

41:44.664 --> 41:47.167
I'm just gettin' started
At the bureau, plus--

41:47.167 --> 41:49.669
[ breathes deeply ]
You're not supposed
To make life decisions...

41:49.669 --> 41:51.505
Until you've got
Some time sober.

41:51.505 --> 41:54.424
That's for 12 months, diane.
You already got 18.

41:54.424 --> 41:58.228
Yeah, well, just worrying
About this, i thought about
Drinkin' a few times.

41:58.228 --> 42:00.680
Oh, well, there it is.

42:01.181 --> 42:04.184
Th-that's the closeout, right?
I mean, i keep up after that,
I'm a jerk.

42:05.519 --> 42:07.988
I'm trying to be honest
About my feelings.

42:08.488 --> 42:10.323
Diane, just say
"i don't want to."

42:10.323 --> 42:12.859
I'm saying doing it now
Doesn't feel right.
Don't tell me what to say.

42:12.859 --> 42:15.028
Okay.

42:15.028 --> 42:17.280
[ sighs ]

42:21.668 --> 42:25.872
-look what it's already
 Done to us.
-yeah? Well, let's kick its ass.

42:54.284 --> 42:56.286
[ sighs ]

42:56.286 --> 42:59.239
So, it was 'cause of me
You had him run those tests?

42:59.239 --> 43:02.042
Andy, you lost a son.

43:05.629 --> 43:08.548
I keep being afraid
Something's gonna
Happen to him,

43:08.548 --> 43:11.551
Or it'll happen to me
And i won't have been able
To keep care of you.

43:14.554 --> 43:17.057
[ sighs ]
I, uh,

43:17.057 --> 43:19.559
Wanna take
Some weight off.

43:19.559 --> 43:21.895
And then he gets sick,
And i'm too worried
To start the diet.

43:21.895 --> 43:24.564
But now we know
They're just colds.

43:26.399 --> 43:30.353
There,
I definitely feel better--
His clean bill of health.

43:31.855 --> 43:34.858
And... Today,
I went after a guy.

43:36.359 --> 43:39.362
I been concerned
I'll be shot.

43:39.362 --> 43:41.865
But today,
I held my end up,

43:41.865 --> 43:44.367
And i didn't
Let bobby down.

43:44.367 --> 43:46.453
So that's progress too.

43:54.094 --> 43:56.096
Remember making love?

43:58.598 --> 44:00.600
What are you suggesting?
[ chuckles ]

44:13.146 --> 44:15.148
I'd hate to wake him up.

44:17.651 --> 44:20.654
Well, just don't beat your chest
And do your jungle yell.

44:24.157 --> 44:27.661
Yeah. I guess
I could leave that out.

44:27.661 --> 44:29.963
[ chuckles ]

